===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|perfit|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|parfit|lang=fro}} (modern: {{term|parfait|lang=fr}}), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|perfectus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|perficere||to finish|lang=la}}, from {{term|per-||through, thorough|lang=la}} + {{term|facere||to do, to make|lang=la}}. Spelling modified 15c. to conform Latin etymology.

